article.description: Davell Roby scored 23 points and grabbed eight rebounds as Saint Louis turned away La Salle in an Atlantic 10 Conference battle Wednesday night.
article.headline: Roby's 23 points spark Saint Louis past La Salle, 70-55
article.linkText: Roby's 23 points spark Saint Louis past La Salle, 70-55
article.story: ST. LOUIS -- Davell Roby scored 23 points and grabbed eight rebounds as Saint Louis turned away La Salle in an Atlantic 10 Conference battle Wednesday night. The Billikens avoid a series sweep after falling at La Salle, 75-54 in January. Saint Louis (11-19, 6-11) took the lead for good on a 3-pointer by Zeke Moore with 9:13 left in the first half and by halftime the Billikens had extended the lead to 36-28. Roby hit 7 of 14 shots from the field, including 4 of 8 from 3-point range. Aaron Hines contributed 12 points and Jalen Johnson grabbed 10 rebounds. Overall Saint Louis was 22 of 57 from the field, including 9 of 26 from distance. Pookie Powell had 17 points for the Explorers (14-14, 8-9), who shot 16 for 56 from the field (28.6 percent), including 4 of 26 from distance. Saint Louis closes out the regular season at Richmond Saturday. La Salle returns home to host Fordham.
